        <abstract> 
<p>Thanks him for his letter in <hi rend="italic">Nature</hi> [23 (1880–1): 336, concerning Samuel Butler’s <hi rend="italic">Unconscious Memory</hi>]. Explains how revision in Krause’s part [of <hi rend="italic">Erasmus Darwin</hi>] and the subsequent misunderstanding came about.</p> 
